# .dockerignore — trims the build context for packaging/zeta/Dockerfile.
#
# Repo root is the build context (Dockerfile needs agent/, adrs/, scripts/,
# packaging/zeta/, agent/vendor/pi/CHECKSUMS). Without these ignore rules,
# BuildKit would transfer .git/, .review/, drafts/, etc. — bloating context
# and risking secrets-in-layers (docker does not read .gitignore).

# --- VCS ------------------------------------------------------------------
**/.git
**/.github
**/.gitignore
**/.gitattributes

# --- Editor / OS noise ----------------------------------------------------
**/.DS_Store
**/.idea
**/.vscode
**/*.swp
**/*~

# --- Lint / CI metadata ---------------------------------------------------
**/.markdownlint-cli2.yaml
**/.markdownlintignore
**/.shellcheckrc

# --- Tier 3 artifacts (NEVER merge to image) ------------------------------
.review/

# --- Local cache / dev clutter --------------------------------------------
**/.cache/
**/node_modules/
**/dist/
**/build/
**/coverage/
**/*.log

# --- Pi runtime data that must never leak into an image layer -------------
agent/auth.json
agent/bin/
agent/sessions/
agent/logs/
agent/cache/
agent/tmp/
agent/models.json
agent/keybindings.json

# --- Vendored binaries: keep OUT of the runtime image (security-review LOW # 2) ---
# The fetcher stage explicitly needs agent/vendor/pi/CHECKSUMS to verify the
# pi binary download; the runtime stage must not bake vendored binaries into
# the published OCI artifact (bloats SBOM, expands supply-chain attack surface
# of the cosign-signed pack per ADR-0014 amendment 2).
agent/vendor/**
!agent/vendor/pi/
!agent/vendor/pi/CHECKSUMS

# --- Common secret-bearing dotfiles (security-review LOW # 1) -------------
# Defense-in-depth against a contributor accidentally dropping any of these
# into the working tree; they would otherwise bake into /repo/agent/ or
# /repo/scripts/ in the runtime image and be redistributed via the signed
# OCI artifact. Zero-cost; repo currently does not contain any of these.
**/.env
**/.env.*
**/.envrc
**/*.pem
**/*.key
**/id_rsa*
**/id_ed25519*
**/.aws/
**/.azure/
**/.config/gh/
**/.npmrc
**/.netrc

# --- Other packaging dirs (when they exist) -------------------------------
# Guard against future packaging/<other-substrate>/ dirs bloating the ζ
# build context. Re-include packaging/zeta/ explicitly.
packaging/*
!packaging/zeta/
